com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util

Class PropagatorFunctionAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.impl.AdapterImpl
      • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util.PropagatorFunctionAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Adapter, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Adapter.Internal

    public class PropagatorFunctionAdapter
extends org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.impl.AdapterImpl
    The objet adapter used by the framework for a PropagatorFunction. Implements the binding with the data elements. There are two kinds of bindings: inbound and outbound binding. An inbound binding binds the PropagatorFunction to some input data element (input of the derivation) while an outbond binding binds the PropagatorFunction to some output data element (output of the derivation).

    Inbound bindings listen to changes in the target object of this adapter by implementing the method InboundBinding#notifyChanged(Notification) and call PropagatorFunctionAdapter#touch when some change in the bound feature occurred.

    Outbound bindings implement the method OutboundBinding#isOutboundBinding(Object), allowing the framework to query if some feature of this adapter is set (out-bound) by the PropagatorFunction.

    Two standard inbound bindings are provided. A InboundBindingFeature, binding to some feature of this propagator's Notifier and an InboundBindingNavigationFeature, binding to some navigation feature , and propagating the binding to the referred object by receiving a Bindings. These standards Inbound bindings can be added with the convenience methods Bindings.addInboundBinding(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EStructuralFeature) and Bindings.addInboundBinding(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EReference, Bindings) respectively.

    One standard outbound binding is provided. An OutboundBindingFeature, binding to some feature of this propagator's Notifier. This standards Outbound binding can be added with the convenience methods Bindings.addOutboundBinding(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EStructuralFeature).

    Registering the PropagatorFunctionAdapters is done by the method PropagatorFunction.enable(), called when listening begins, that is when the PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter is added to the notifier. Unregistering the PropagatorFunctionAdapters is done by the method PropagatorFunction.disable(), called when the adapter manager is removed from the Notifier.
